ith-the-british-at-the-battle-of-bunker-hill-archaeologists-are-uncovering-evidence-of-the-fighting-251-years-later-180988979/</link><description>研究人员在波士顿查尔斯顿附近发现了枪支零件、步枪子弹和其他文物</description><pubDate>Thu, 18 Jun 2026 10:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/in-june-1775-the-american-patriots-faced-off-with-the-british-at-the-battle-of-bunker-hill-archaeologists-are-uncovering-evidence-of-the-fighting-251-years-later-180988979/</guid></item><item><title>在国王曾经居住过的英国寄宿学校发现了可追溯到亨利八世统治时期的隐藏隧道</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hidden-tunnels-dating-back-to-henry-viiis-reign-were-discovered-at-english-boarding-school-New-Hall-School-where-the-king-once-lived-180988965/</link><description>在新霍尔学校（曾经是亨利八世的博利厄宫）发现了骨头、瓶子和陶器。在此之前，安妮·博林的父亲拥有该庄园</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:56:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/hidden-tunnels-dating-back-to-henry-viiis-reign-were-discovered-at-english-boarding-school-New-Hall-School-where-the-king-once-lived-180988965/</guid></item><item><title>科学家在巴布亚新几内亚发现了一种新的“行走”鲨鱼。他们怀疑它有灭绝的危险</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-discover-a-new-species-of-walking-shark-in-papua-new-guinea-they-suspect-its-at-risk-of-going-extinct-180988977/</link><description>这种生物属于一个独特的鲨鱼群体，其成员可以使用像腿一样强壮的胸鳍来四处走动</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 20:41:10 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-discover-a-new-species-of-walking-shark-in-papua-new-guinea-they-suspect-its-at-risk-of-going-extinct-180988977/</guid></item><item><title>考古学家在美国独立战争第一次进攻胜利所在地提康德罗加堡出土了数百件文物</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-hundreds-of-artifacts-at-fort-ticonderoga-the-site-of-americas-first-offensive-victory-of-the-revolutionary-war-180988971/</link><description>这些物品是在自由山发现的，许多大陆军士兵就是在那里第一次听到《独立宣言》的文本的</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 18:54:33 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/archaeologists-unearth-hundreds-of-artifacts-at-fort-ticonderoga-the-site-of-americas-first-offensive-victory-of-the-revolutionary-war-180988971/</guid></item><item><title>为庆祝其生日，美国将向未来的美国人赠送一个重达 900 磅的时间胶囊，里面装满了艺术品、自然宝藏和精美的《独立宣言》副本</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/indigenous-art-an-eagle-feather-and-a-3d-rendering-of-abraham-lincolns-hand-see-the-items-just-sealed-in-americas-time-capsule-180988973/</link><description>该胶囊是在国会的指导下通过 America250 委员会创建和填充的。它将于 7 月 4 日被埋葬在原来的雕塑下面</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 17:20:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/indigenous-art-an-eagle-feather-and-a-3d-rendering-of-abraham-lincolns-hand-see-the-items-just-sealed-in-americas-time-capsule-180988973/</guid></item><item><title>澳大利亚城市的雄性园丁鸟将人类垃圾变成宝藏，以打动潜在的配偶</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/male-bowerbirds-in-australian-cities-are-turning-human-trash-into-treasure-to-impress-potential-mates-180988969/</link><description>一项新的研究表明，即使是乡村鸟类在选择人造物体（例如彩色玻璃和金属丝）和自然装饰品（例如树叶和贝壳）时也更喜欢它们</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 15:35:56 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/male-bowerbirds-in-australian-cities-are-turning-human-trash-into-treasure-to-impress-potential-mates-180988969/</guid></item><item><title>临床试验表明，这种“改变实践”的基因测试可以告诉医生哪些乳腺癌患者可以跳过化疗</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-practice-changing-gene-test-could-tell-doctors-which-patients-with-breast-cancer-can-skip-chemo-clinical-trial-suggests-180988957/</link><description>化疗会带来使人衰弱的副作用，包括脑雾、恶心和神经损伤。新研究表明，许多患有常见类型乳腺癌的人只需要放射治疗和激素治疗即可预防复发</description><pubDate>Wed, 17 Jun 2026 14:01:52 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/this-practice-changing-gene-test-could-tell-doctors-which-patients-with-breast-cancer-can-skip-chemo-clinical-trial-suggests-180988957/</guid></item><item><title>科学家发现了关于北爱尔兰标志性地质结构巨人堤道火山起源的新线索</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-uncover-new-clues-about-the-volcanic-origins-of-the-giants-causeway-an-iconic-geologic-structure-in-northern-ireland-180988967/</link><description>这个被联合国教科文组织列为世界遗产的遗址拥有 40,000 根近乎完美的六角柱，形成于大约 6000 万年前的激烈火山活动时期</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 21:32:25 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-uncover-new-clues-about-the-volcanic-origins-of-the-giants-causeway-an-iconic-geologic-structure-in-northern-ireland-180988967/</guid></item><item><title>欣赏美国宇航局宇航员捕捉到的南极光在地球上舞动的壮丽景色</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-a-stunning-view-of-the-southern-lights-dancing-across-the-earth-captured-by-a-nasa-astronaut-180988960/</link><description>NASA SpaceX Crew-12 任务指挥官杰西卡·梅尔分享了她在国际空间站外的太空舱中避难时拍摄的绿色极光的照片和视频</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 16:04:53 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-a-stunning-view-of-the-southern-lights-dancing-across-the-earth-captured-by-a-nasa-astronaut-180988960/</guid></item><item><title>观看科苏梅尔难以捉摸的矮狐的第一张照片，它是世界上最稀有的犬科动物之一</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-first-ever-photographs-of-cozumels-elusive-dwarf-fox-one-of-the-rarest-canids-in-the-world-180988961/</link><description>二十多年来没有人见过这些生物，导致科学家怀疑它们是否已经灭绝。这种情况在 2023 年 9 月发生了变化</description><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-first-ever-photographs-of-cozumels-elusive-dwarf-fox-one-of-the-rarest-canids-in-the-world-180988961/</guid></item><item><title>您现在可以在费城看到贝特西·罗斯 (Betsy Ross) 的缝纫台，感谢她的曾曾曾曾孙在卖旗日的捐赠</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/you-can-now-see-betsy-ross-sewing-table-in-philadelphia-thanks-to-a-flag-day-donation-from-her-great-great-great-great-grandson-180988963/</link><description>星条旗的起源尚不清楚，但几代美国人都钦佩罗斯创造第一面美国国旗的